genresAdvancedInfo.name: rap ecuatoguineano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Rap ecuatoguineano is a form of hip hop that originated in Equatorial Guinea. It is characterized by its use of Spanish and Portuguese lyrics, as well as traditional African rhythms and instruments. The genre has gained popularity in recent years, with artists such as Kachafayah and Don Dinero leading the way.
